Package edu.sru.thangiah.datastructures.generic.tree.redblacktree

Class RedBlackTreeGeneric<T extends Comparable<? super T>>

java.lang.Object
edu.sru.thangiah.datastructures.generic.AbstractTreeGeneric<T>
edu.sru.thangiah.datastructures.generic.tree.redblacktree.RedBlackTreeGeneric<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
BaseOpsGeneric<T>, TreeOpsGeneric<T>
public class RedBlackTreeGeneric<T extends Comparable<? super T>> extends AbstractTreeGeneric<T>

Title: RedBlackTreeGeneric

Description:

Generic implementation for an Red Black tree which allows the user to create instances with any data type. Note that a Red Black Tree tree is a self-balancing tree which checks the colors of the nodes in the subtrees to ensure equal distancing of nodes and minimal search time
Version:
1.0
Author:
Sam R. Thangiah
